youts/compare/v1-layout...v2-layout"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"the diff"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for details on exactly what changed."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"why-change-the-layouts"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#why-change-the-layouts","ariaLabel":"why change the layouts permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Why change the layouts?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Looking at the difference in code, it might be tempting to think, “Doesn’t that just create "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"more work"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for developers who want to use layouts?”"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In short, the decision to remove layouts was part of an effort to reduce unnecessary complexity and mystery issues in Gatsby projects."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"what-was-the-unnecessary-complexity"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#what-was-the-unnecessary-complexity","ariaLabel":"what was the unnecessary complexity permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"What was the unnecessary complexity?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Because layouts in V1 were applied under the hood, it made it "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"really hard"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to pass data between the layout and the pages it wrapped."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In short, layouts in V1 broke React’s compositional model, and that made things unnecessarily hard to implement. By going back to the standard React way of importing components and using them directly, we’re able to easily pass data between the layout and pages without any confusing, complicated, or otherwise unwieldy workarounds."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"what-are-mystery-issues"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#what-are-mystery-issues","ariaLabel":"what are mystery issues permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"What are mystery issues?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In V1, if something breaks on your page, you’d likely go to the page, look through the code, and try to spot the bug. But what if the bug is in the magic layout component? That component isn’t referenced anywhere on the page, and if you don’t "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"already know"}]},{"type":"text","value":" that Gatsby V1 wraps pages with layouts, it’s pretty difficult to figure out what’s going on."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Because Gatsby is doing things in the background, out of sight of the developers building the site, we’re creating a mystery: where the hell did this bug come from if all the code I can see doesn’t have the bug?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"By removing the magic and making layouts an explicit dependency in V2, that same bug would be much easier to spot because there’s a clear link between our page code and the layout."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"why-is-this-better"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#why-is-this-better","ariaLabel":"why is this better permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Why is this better?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Our goal at Gatsby is to make building great apps more fun and less frustrating — and "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"very few things"}]},{"type":"text","value":" are more frustrating than mystery bugs."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This change reduces the number of mysteries in your Gatsby projects, and makes debugging a little simpler."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"what-else-is-changing"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#what-else-is-changing","ariaLabel":"what else is changing permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"What else is changing?"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Removing layouts isn’t the only improvement coming in Gatsby V2. We’re really excited to introduce a lot of new and exciting features, such as:"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Much faster hot reloading, which enables Ludicrous Mode"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{"className":["twitter-tweet"],"dataLang":"en"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{"lang":"en","dir":"ltr"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Coming soon to Gatsby v2: Ludicrous mode data hot reloading ;-)"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://t.co/by1PyOYXc0"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://t.co/by1PyOYXc0"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tagName":"br","properties":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"(note, this gif is not sped up at all) "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://t.co/hFIYMbpalN"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"pic.twitter.com/hFIYMbpalN"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"— Gatsby (@gatsbyjs) "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://twitter.com/gatsbyjs/status/974507205121617920?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"March 16, 2018"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We can now add GraphQL 